WEBVTT

01:03.272 --> 01:05.566
- Good dog.
- Vogel!

01:05.649 --> 01:07.068
My little dove.

01:07.693 --> 01:09.820
Are we expecting guests?

01:09.904 --> 01:13.115
Indeed we are.
Even a famous poet.

01:14.200 --> 01:16.160
Wonderful.
What does he write?

01:18.162 --> 01:20.414
He has written
about a marquise

01:21.332 --> 01:25.044
who, while unconscious,
is impregnated by an unknown man

01:25.127 --> 01:27.421
and then discovers
that the unknown man

01:27.505 --> 01:30.674
is the man she thought
she was in love with.

01:31.258 --> 01:33.677
And consequently she
can no longer love him.

01:35.930 --> 01:40.518
That sounds rather strange.
Incidents of that kind rarely happen.

01:42.561 --> 01:45.272
Yet I find the fate of
the marquise moving.

01:46.732 --> 01:48.859
As if I were her.

01:50.277 --> 01:53.781
Well then, he must be
a truly outstanding poet,

01:53.864 --> 01:57.535
if his writings give you
such a curious idea!

02:19.431 --> 02:24.019
<i>A violet in the meadow stood</i>

02:24.103 --> 02:29.108
<i>With humble brow,
demure and good</i>

02:29.733 --> 02:34.905
<i>It was the sweetest violet</i>

02:35.739 --> 02:39.577
<i>There came along
a shepherdess</i>

02:39.660 --> 02:43.330
<i>With youthful step
and happiness</i>

02:43.414 --> 02:49.003
<i>Who sang
Who sang along the way</i>

02:49.086 --> 02:52.756
<i>This song</i>

03:00.764 --> 03:04.685
<i>Oh!
Thought the violet</i>

03:05.746 --> 03:11.422
<i>How I pine for nature's
beauty to be mine</i>

03:11.817 --> 03:16.822
<i>If only for a moment</i>

03:17.448 --> 03:21.035
<i>For then my love
might notice me</i>

03:21.118 --> 03:25.206
<i>And on her bosom fasten me</i>

03:25.289 --> 03:27.291
<i>Oh, I wish</i>

03:27.374 --> 03:33.135
<i>Oh, I wish if only
for a moment long</i>

03:36.675 --> 03:39.511
<i>But, cruel fate!</i>

03:39.595 --> 03:42.097
<i>The maiden came</i>

03:42.806 --> 03:46.060
<i>Without a glance
or care for it</i>

03:46.143 --> 03:50.940
<i>She trampled
down the violet</i>

03:51.899 --> 03:54.568
<i>It sank</i>

03:54.652 --> 03:57.738
<i>And died</i>

03:57.821 --> 04:02.368
<i>But happily</i>

04:02.451 --> 04:07.915
<i>And so I die then
let me die for her</i>

04:07.998 --> 04:09.750
<i>For her</i>

04:09.833 --> 04:15.256
<i>Beneath her darling feet</i>

04:19.510 --> 04:22.930
<i>Poor little violet</i>

04:23.764 --> 04:29.728
<i>It was the sweetest violet</i>

04:39.571 --> 04:41.532
Simply to die for!

04:53.043 --> 04:56.755
- She is an admirer of your marquise.
- Really?

04:56.839 --> 05:00.050
Oh, I wouldn't
call it admiration.

05:01.343 --> 05:04.388
Which woman has
experienced such a fate?

05:04.471 --> 05:07.808
That is what makes
the story so appealing.

05:07.891 --> 05:11.854
To read something one would
never wish to experience,

05:11.937 --> 05:15.232
and yet, bizarrely,
one yearns to imagine it all the same.

05:16.817 --> 05:19.361
I try to describe
what engenders fear,

05:19.987 --> 05:22.698
but perhaps also desire.

05:22.781 --> 05:24.616
Desire?

05:24.700 --> 05:27.703
I would say one has
to accept one's fate.

05:27.786 --> 05:30.664
- No matter how cruel it may be.
- But you said it yourself.

05:31.248 --> 05:33.500
The marquise is appealing.

05:35.169 --> 05:36.670
Yes.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.840
That may often be the case.

05:39.923 --> 05:42.801
You say one thing but
also feel another.

05:43.635 --> 05:46.889
Yes, this may often
be the case.

05:46.972 --> 05:50.225
You think you want to live,
but in fact you want to die.

05:59.693 --> 06:01.403
The poor thing.

06:04.281 --> 06:05.949
Who?

06:06.033 --> 06:07.951
Frau von Krahl.

06:08.035 --> 06:09.870
I feel sorry for her.

06:11.663 --> 06:13.332
Why is that?

06:14.375 --> 06:17.461
It must be terrible to be
such a famous singer,

06:18.003 --> 06:21.131
being exposed to the
opinion of the public.

06:21.548 --> 06:23.801
What if she made a mistake?

06:24.551 --> 06:26.470
It would be so embarrassing.

06:29.306 --> 06:31.308
But everybody admires her.

06:31.975 --> 06:35.687
Yes, but if she makes a mistake,
she will be despised.

06:36.355 --> 06:37.898
People can be so cruel.

06:39.066 --> 06:41.318
But she is famous,
respected.

06:41.402 --> 06:44.279
She has achieved a position.
All by herself.

06:44.363 --> 06:46.073
Nevertheless...

06:47.157 --> 06:50.911
I may have achieved nothing in life
except to take care of you and Pauline.

06:51.662 --> 06:54.957
But that's enough for me.
That's just the way I am.

06:57.251 --> 06:59.461
And how did you
find our poet?

07:00.212 --> 07:01.964
Oh, him.

07:02.965 --> 07:06.343
He seems to have a rather
melancholic disposition.

07:07.428 --> 07:09.430
He depresses me.

07:10.431 --> 07:12.307
But he appears to like you.

07:12.933 --> 07:14.435
Certainly not.

07:18.147 --> 07:20.816
My soul is in such
a precarious state

07:20.899 --> 07:23.777
that when I stick my
nose out of the window

07:23.861 --> 07:26.488
the daylight pains me with
its constant shimmering.

07:27.823 --> 07:31.160
Some people would consider
this an illness or excess tension.

07:31.243 --> 07:32.995
But not you.

07:33.078 --> 07:38.041
You have the ability to see the world
from a perspective other than your own.

07:41.378 --> 07:43.755
I have become so sensitive

07:43.839 --> 07:49.511
that even the smallest of onslaughts
to which my feelings are exposed

07:49.595 --> 07:52.055
causes me the
greatest of suffering.

07:53.098 --> 07:55.601
You are indeed melancholic today.

07:56.768 --> 08:00.272
Perhaps it is your gall that
troubles your soul? Or...

08:00.355 --> 08:03.358
My dearest friend,
it is not my gall,

08:03.442 --> 08:06.862
but the world itself
that troubles my soul.

08:08.989 --> 08:12.367
I know a doctor who understands
the soul thoroughly.

08:12.451 --> 08:16.705
He healed a woman who was blinded
by a shock and now she can see again.

08:18.665 --> 08:21.168
Nothing upon this
earth can help me.

08:22.252 --> 08:24.838
The present has no
appeal for me at all,

08:25.380 --> 08:30.135
and as for the future,
I can only think of the mortifying fact

08:30.219 --> 08:32.304
that it will end one day.

08:38.894 --> 08:44.608
However, what I long for is that you,
Marie, can understand me.

08:45.943 --> 08:48.403
But I do understand you,

08:48.487 --> 08:51.031
you dear and sensitive man.

08:51.114 --> 08:53.700
- Then may I ask something of you?
- Of course.

08:55.744 --> 08:57.788
Would you care
to die with me?

09:00.707 --> 09:02.584
Of course not.

09:05.003 --> 09:07.339
But with pistols it
can be very quick.

09:07.422 --> 09:10.050
First I'd shoot you,
and then myself.

09:10.634 --> 09:13.595
You would make me very,
very happy.

09:14.972 --> 09:17.641
I'm very fond of you,
as you know, my dear.

09:17.724 --> 09:20.310
But now you really
are going too far.

09:20.394 --> 09:24.898
- But I love you, Marie.
- And I love you too, my dear.

09:25.566 --> 09:29.152
Then please do consider my request,
my dearest Marie!

09:29.653 --> 09:31.738
Because I love you.

09:31.822 --> 09:35.826
And if you love me too, really love me,
you will do this for me.

09:36.493 --> 09:39.997
Because nothing in life should be
more important to you than this love.

09:40.455 --> 09:42.332
Not even life itself.

11:02.746 --> 11:05.999
<i>I'm afraid Pauline has
a piano lesson on Tuesday.</i>

11:06.083 --> 11:08.710
<i>I therefore cannot
go for a walk with you.</i>

11:12.756 --> 11:17.177
<i>On Wednesday Vogel has a free afternoon,
so we shall spend the time together.</i>

11:23.016 --> 11:26.061
<i>But if you are
available on Friday,</i>

11:26.144 --> 11:29.523
<i>I would be glad if you would
join us for a musical evening,</i>

11:29.606 --> 11:31.525
<i>at about seven o'clock.</i>

11:36.196 --> 11:38.532
<i>Whatever you wanted
to tell me face to face</i>

11:38.615 --> 11:41.785
<i>can surely be revealed in
the company of others after all.</i>

11:47.624 --> 11:50.502
Tell me, my dear friend,
for surely you know.

11:50.877 --> 11:53.755
It would interest me:
The new tax...

11:55.424 --> 11:57.968
Must absolutely
everybody pay it?

11:58.760 --> 12:00.095
Yes.

12:00.804 --> 12:04.099
- Including the aristocracy?
- Yes.

12:04.182 --> 12:07.060
But also the townsman,
the peasant and the beggar.

12:07.144 --> 12:10.981
The new tax applies to everybody.
That's what's new about it.

12:11.982 --> 12:17.028
And that is why the peasant is to be freed?
Merely so he can pay taxes?

12:17.112 --> 12:20.615
- How unjust.
- But still, it is a rather nice idea.

12:20.699 --> 12:23.618
Freedom and equality
for all before the law.

12:24.327 --> 12:26.455
That is French, is it not?

12:28.123 --> 12:31.293
I believe the peasants would
rather remain in bondage

12:31.376 --> 12:35.338
than be free like their masters
just so they can pay taxes.

12:35.422 --> 12:39.009
That is an undesirable freedom,
which nobody would want.

12:39.092 --> 12:44.264
- They would have to be freed by force.
- Exactly.

12:44.347 --> 12:49.186
How should a serf, who knows nothing
but bondage, survive on his own!

12:49.269 --> 12:51.271
It will be his downfall.

12:51.897 --> 12:53.273
And yet...

12:53.732 --> 12:57.736
I would rather be free and face my
downfall than remain in bondage.

12:58.403 --> 13:00.113
I would not.

13:00.197 --> 13:04.826
I am my husband's property, and I
should never dare to demand freedom.

13:09.372 --> 13:14.294
Our government's attempt to reform
the state according to French ideas

13:14.377 --> 13:17.714
is a mockery of our understanding
of justice and injustice.

13:17.798 --> 13:20.509
What they call equality
is really injustice,

13:20.592 --> 13:23.428
and what they call
freedom is a trick.

13:24.304 --> 13:28.183
Whereas the feudal state has
developed in Prussia over centuries

13:28.266 --> 13:32.103
and represents
the natural order.

13:33.313 --> 13:36.149
Why should we abandon it?

13:37.484 --> 13:40.904
In exchange for the shortsighted
ideas of some dreamers,

13:40.987 --> 13:44.616
who claim to be Republicans
or even Democrats?

13:44.699 --> 13:48.829
Dreamers who have apparently not
noticed that the revolt in France failed!

